Soldiers assigned to the 3rd U.S. Infantry Regiment, known as "The Old Guard," didn't let a little snow keep them from guarding the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier in Arlington National Cemetery, Virginia.
Guarding the Tomb A soldier assigned to the 3rd U.S. Infantry Regiment, known as “The Old Guard,” performs his duty at the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier in Arlington National Cemetery, Va. on a snowy Martin Luther King Jr. Day, Jan. 15, 2024. Share: × Share Copy Link Email Facebook X LinkedIn WhatsApp Download: Full Size ( 3.81 MB ) Photo By: Army Sgt. Ethan Scofield VIRIN: 240115-A-LT474-1003 Snowy Assignment Soldiers assigned to the 3rd U.S. Infantry Regiment, known as “The Old Guard,” perform their duties at the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier in Arlington National Cemetery, Va. on a snowy Martin Luther King Jr. Day, Jan. 15, 2024. Share: × Share Copy Link Email Facebook X LinkedIn WhatsApp Download: Full Size ( 1.77 MB ) Photo By: Army Sgt. Ethan Scofield VIRIN: 240115-A-LT474-1019Y
